Dancing is a fun way to stay fit and improve balance, coordination, and cardiovascular health. You can dance at home, join a class, or go to social dances. Choose music you enjoy and start with a warm-up: move gently to the music for five minutes. Gradually increase the intensity, incorporating more vigorous movements. Dance for 20-30 minutes, taking breaks as needed. Always cool down with gentle movements for five minutes to let your heart rate return to normal. Dancing can also be a wonderful social activity, providing both physical and emotional benefits.

• Choose music you enjoy.
• Start with a warm-up by moving gently to the music for five minutes.
• Gradually increase the intensity with more vigorous movements.
• Dance for 20-30 minutes, taking breaks as needed.
• Cool down with gentle movements for five minutes.
